<p>I've given the OU Annotate bookmarklet a try, and so far it looks impressive. I'm particularly happy to see the functionality to export annotations in various formats, including to Google Docs - intriguing. I would also welcome the option to publish an RSS/Atom feed of my personal annotations. I'm a fairly heavy Delicious user. If it was possible to make annotations world readable (probably a big ask), or if anyone who self-registers for a <a href="https://msds.open.ac.uk/SAMSWebSelfRegistrationNet/SAMSDefault/SAMS006_Default.aspx">free Open University account</a> could use OU Annotate I'd consider switching.</p>
<p>Personally, I think that OU Annotate would be a great marketing tool for the OU.</p>]]></description>
