              <title>ODET 2010: Dan Prager - bCisive Online</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3961</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3961</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><a href="/cloud/www.bcisiveonline.com">bCisive Online</a> is a web-based decision-making and collaboration tool from <a href="/cloud/www.austhink.com">Austhink Software</a>. &nbsp;&nbsp;It &nbsp;follows on from our previous commercial forays into desk-top-based visual mapping software:&nbsp;the business-oriented&nbsp;<a href="/cloud/bcisive.austhink.com">bCisive desktop</a>, and before that the argument-mapping-based&nbsp;<a href="/cloud/rationale.austhink.com">Rationale</a>. &nbsp;</p>
<p>In developing&nbsp;bCisive Online we aimed to make visual thinking and deliberation both simpler and more team-oriented. &nbsp;Probably the most striking innovation is a form of <a href="http://bcisiveonline.blogspot.com/2010/02/real-time-collaboration-overview.html">real-time collaboration</a>. &nbsp;Multiple participants can collaboratively edit a map: remotely manipulated boxes fly around in near real-time, echoing multiplayer online games, while "control" (the ability to edit) is passed around in a disciplined fashion.</p>
<p>In this talk I would like to explain the motivation for introducing real-time collaboration, and its design and realisation in bCisive Online.</p>]]></description>
