                    <item>
              <title>SocialLearn session: OU&#39;s Learning &amp; Tech Conf. 2010</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3122</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/3122</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<p><strong>[<a href="http://projects.kmi.open.ac.uk/sociallearn/SocialLearn-Talk-OU2010.mov" target="_blank">Replay SocialLearn presentation</a>]</strong></p>
<p><strong>Welcome</strong> to our cloud for this conference session :-)&nbsp;from the&nbsp;SocialLearn team: Simon Buckingham Shum, Rebecca Ferguson, Mark Glaister, Thanh Le&nbsp;</p>
<p>SocialLearn (part of the portfolio under Denise Kirkpatrick, Pro-Vice Chancellor for Learning &amp; Teaching Quality) is designing a social learning space which can integrate existing tools in the OU and the cloud, to support learning.&nbsp;Our immediate target groups are the hundreds of thousands of users in the Open University&rsquo;s online communities, with a specific focus in the coming year on professional development and e-scholarship/research.</p>
