              <title>The AUTC Learning Design Project on ICT-based learning designs</title>
              <link>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/14</link>
              <guid>https://cloudworks.ac.uk/cloud/view/14</guid>
              <description><![CDATA[<img src="/files/autc.jpg" width="341" height="316" />
<b>A rich set of examples of learning designs for role play, collaboration, concept development, problem-based learning, case studies</b>
<p>
You can use the web site resources to develop high quality learning experiences for students by:
</p>
<p>
1. exploring a range of proven learning designs, with exemplar aspects and full instructions on how to implement the designs (exemplars)
</p>
<p>
2. examining a set of generic learning designs to apply in your knowledge domain (guides)
</p>
<p>
3. making use of a set of tools for supporting learners (tools)
</p>
<p>
4. reviewing the principles for design of high quality learning experiences (the project)
</p>
